Castle Toward was commissioned as HMS Brontosaurus in 1942 . 
  The 19th century castle near Dunoon was used to ready troops for the D-Day landings of 1944 . 
  Overlooking the Clyde estuary and with easy access to the shoreline , it was used as a training base for troops . 
  Soldiers practised beach landings and many were killed in training accidents  . 
